article_title: Must-see morning clip: “Saturday Night Live” mocks Kim Jong-un’s mysterious absence
article_text:
Topics: bobby moynihan, Diabetes, gout, Kim Jong-un, Saturday Night Live, Video, Entertainment News, News

Last night’s “Saturday Night Live” cold opening turned its attention to Kim Jong-un, the supreme leader of North Korea who has gone missing in the past few weeks, many assume due to extreme illness including diabetes and gout.

Kim Jong-un, played by Bobby Moynihan, cleared up any misunderstandings on Saturday, declaring “I am as strong as a dragon!” as he quietly sobs attempting to climb stairs.

Watch the clip below to learn how the supreme leader actually broke both his ankles.
